    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-02T16:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-02T16:30:00-05:00" n="823"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6363/324: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-02T17:30:00-04:00"
                            >April 2, 1943—5:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A−672. Embassy’s 575, March 24, 1943.<note n="49" xml:id="d823fn49">Not
                        printed.</note> It is desirable to keep Chile’s quotas of diesel oil and
                    fuel oil as near 40 percent of 1941 consumption as possible, and it is suggested
                    that you obtain from the Chilean authorities their estimated over-all minimum
                    requirements for both diesel and fuel oils and submit them here for
                    consideration by the Essentials Committee<note n="50" xml:id="d823fn50"
                        >Essentials Requirements Committee, an interagency organization authorized
                        to present requests for critical materials.</note> before you begin
                    discussions of individual categories.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
